org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.events

Class InitEventMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.Message
      • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.BaseMessage
        • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.events.EventMessage
          • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.events.InitEventMessage

  • public class InitEventMessage
extends EventMessage
    An InitEventMessage is type of EventMessage that stores information from a part of code being initialized.
    The arguments passed through the constructor are given as an array of objects and logged as data to the "args" key as a JsonArray.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      InitEventMessage(java.lang.Object source, java.lang.String name, java.lang.Object[] arguments)
      Creates a new initialization message with the arguments used during initialization passed through the constructor as the key "args" and appends the init tag to the "type" key.
